\section desc Description
Common algorihtm specific for \ref DataFormats_Candidate "Candidate" types
with \ref RecoPackages "Reco" components.

\subsection interface Public interface
None.
\subsection modules Modules
- ChargedCandidateProducer: produces a collection of reco::Candidate with a reco::Track component.
The default configuration file <tt>AllTracks.cfi</tt> is the following:
<pre>
\htmlinclude allTracks.cfi
</pre>
- EcalCandidateProducer: produces a collection of reco::Candidate with a reco::SuperCluster component.
The default configuration file <tt>AllSuperClusters.cfi</tt> is the following:
<pre>
\htmlinclude allSuperClusters.cfi
</pre>

For the above producers one (and only one) of the following parameters must
be specified in order to set the particle mass hypothesis:
\htmlonly
<pre>
  string particleType = "pi+"
</pre>
\endhtmlonly
or:
\htmlonly
<pre>
  int32 particleId = 211
</pre>
\endhtmlonly
or:
\htmlonly
<pre>
  double particleMass = 0.13957
</pre>
\endhtmlonly
If a particle type or paricle ID is specified to determine the mass value,
a PDT service must be loaded in the configuration file.

\subsection othermodules Modules from other packages
- CaloTowerCandidateCreator (from \ref RecoLocalCalo_CaloTowersCreator "RecoLocalCalo/CaloTowersCreator"): produces a collection of reco::Candidate with CaloTower component.

